I immediately fell in love after one bite of the creme brulee. Then I tried the  coconut coffee and knew this was going to be my favorite place so far in Hanoi. Try these two and you will agree. I also tried the chicken fruit salad which was light and delicious. The atmosphere inside is so cute and quaint. If I ever come back to Hanoi I will definitely come back here. They have a little guest book that you can sign too. I will never forget this place❤️

Thank you so much for your kind words and heartfelt review!

We’re truly delighted to hear that our crème brûlée and coconut coffee made such a memorable impression — they’re two of our favorites as well! It means a lot to us that Xofa could become your special spot in Hanoi, even just for a little while.

We're also glad you enjoyed the chicken fruit salad and felt comfortable in our cozy little corner. The guest book has captured so many beautiful stories, and we're honored to have yours among them.

Should your journey ever bring you back to Hanoi, we’d love nothing more than to welcome you again. Until then, thank you for making us a part of your memories. ❤️

Warmest wishes,
The Xofa Team.

The food was delicious, and the service was friendly and attentive. We especially loved the variety of drinks and the welcoming vibe that makes you want to stay for hours.

Your support means the world to us, and we can’t wait to welcome you back for another wonderful experience! ☕💛

Warm regards,

Tucked away in the heart of Hanoi’s Old Quarter, just a stone’s throw from the iconic Train Street, this cozy garden café was the perfect spot for a peaceful breakfast. We ordered a classic morning meal that met every expectation—simple, fresh, and delicious. The coffee, however, truly stood out—rich, aromatic, and possibly the best we had in the city.

The service was another highlight. The staff were warm, welcoming, and made us feel right at home from the moment we walked in. The garden setting added an extra layer of charm to the experience—lush, quiet, and beautifully maintained, it was a lovely escape from the city’s bustle.

Highly recommended for anyone seeking a relaxed breakfast with great coffee and genuine hospitality in the Old Quarter.

Thank you for such a beautifully written and thoughtful review — we’re genuinely touched! It’s wonderful to hear that you enjoyed the breakfast, especially the coffee, and that the garden setting brought a sense of calm to your morning.

Our team always aims to provide a warm and welcoming experience, and we’re so glad it came through during your visit. Your recommendation means the world to us, and we hope to welcome you back to our cozy corner of the Old Quarter soon. 🌿☕🍳

A Heartfelt Return at Xofa and Bistro

After eight years abroad, coming back to Vietnam and visiting Xofa and Bistro was a warm and refreshing experience. Greeted with big smiles from Quynh and Linh Huy, I instantly felt at home. My waiter, Linh, was not only helpful but genuinely funny—she made the evening even more enjoyable.

I ordered an oolong tea and chocolate, a surprisingly delightful combo that was perfectly crafted by the talented bar team: Tung, Anh Hung, and Dat. Big shoutout to them—the drink was smooth, balanced, and memorable.

Xofa isn’t just about good drinks; it’s about people who care. I left reminded of what makes Hanoi’s hospitality so special.

Welcome back to Vietnam! We're so honored to be part of your return experience. We're thrilled you had a warm welcome and enjoyed your time at Xofa. It’s always our aim to create a space where you feel at home. We’ll be sure to pass along your kind words to Quynh, Linh Huy, Linh, and the talented bar team. Looking forward to having you back soon! 🌿💛

Sincerely,
The Xofa Team.
